are derived from Late Latin <i>abbas</i> (genitive <i>abbatis</i>) ‘priest’, from Greek <i>abbas</i>, from Aramaic <i>aba</i> ‘father’. The nickname was presumably a joking reference to a person's behaviour. In the US, the English name is also sometimes a translation of a cognate or equivalent European name, e.g. Italian   Abate  , Spanish   Abad  , or German   Abt  .","History: George Abbot from Yorkshire, England, settled in Andover, MA, in 1640; he had numerous prominent descendants. George Abbott (probably not the same man) died in Rowley, MA, in 1647. Another early migrant was James Abbott, who came from Somerset, England, to Long Island, NY, in the 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Abate","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Antonio, Carmelo, Carmine, Gaetano, Vito, Angelo, Canio, Rocco, Sal, Aldo, Carlo.","Italian: from <i>abate</i> ‘priest’ (from Late Latin <i>abbas</i> ‘priest’, genitive <i>abbatis</i>). It could be a nickname, perhaps given to someone who behaved in a priest-like manner, an occupational name for the servant of a priest, or it may denote an (illegitimate) son of a priest. Compare   Labate  ."]},{"name":"Abbot","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Abbott  . The spelling with one <i>-t</i> is more typically Scottish than English, and in Gaelic-speaking areas of Scotland, this is sometimes an Anglicized form of   McNabb  ."]},{"name":"Abbitt","meanings":["English: variant of   Abbott  ."]},{"name":"Abbett","meanings":["English: variant of   Abbott  ."]},{"name":"Abbotts","meanings":["English:","topographic or occupational name from Middle English <i>(atte) abbotes</i> ‘(at the, of the) abbot's (house or quarters)’, a name for someone who lived or worked at such a place, presumably a servant.","variant of   Abbott  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Abbott II was born in 1336, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with John Abbott. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1336–":"1336–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"umbes 1435","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1336–":"1336–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"noin 1435","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1336–":"1336–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1336–Female":"1336–Décédée","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"environ 1435","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Abbott II est née en 1336, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John Abbott. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1336–":"1336–Verstorben","1330–Male":"1330–Verstorben","1435–1490":"1435–1490","1336–Female":"1336–Verstorben","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1330":"1330","1490":"1490","c.1435":"um 1435","Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs. John Abbott II wurde 1336 in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit John Abbott mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in ihrem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1336–":"1336–Desede","1330–Male":"1330–Desed